window.bookSummaryJSON = "<p>The fifth in the new Naxos audioooks series \"In a Nutshell\", <i>The French Revolution</i> is a short and accessible introduction to one of the most important periods in European history. It brings vividly to life the implacable Robespierre, the frightened Marie Antoinette and the iconic image of the guillotine. But it also demonstrates the key role the Revolution played in the development of European politics.</p>"; 
